cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is about semi-supervised semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a method that involves learning a second task related to semantic segmentation, which is a machine learning task. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves predicting probability maps and using them as a supervision signal, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses a two-branch network, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
